The paper proposes a deep learning model for music source separation using convolutional neural networks with skip connections and recurrent layers. This work is related to signal processing (cs.SD) and speech processing (cs.SI). The use of convolutional neural networks and enhancement modules suggests that the paper may also be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and neural networks (cs.NE).
